## 2. Files that define / orchestrate the environment\
\
### 2.1 Shell\uc0\u8209 level environment (where values actually live)\
\
These values are **not** committed to the repo; you define them in your shell (e.g. `~/.zshrc`) or export them before running scripts:\
\
- `CLOUD_SQL_PROXY_CREDENTIAL_FILE`  \
  - Optional, used by `scripts/dev-start.sh` to run `cloud-sql-proxy` with a dedicated service account key.  \
  - Example from the script comments:\
    - `export CLOUD_SQL_PROXY_CREDENTIAL_FILE="$HOME/.gcp-keys/nexus-dev-proxy-key.json"`\
\
- `DEV_DB_PASSWORD`  \
  - Used by `scripts/dev-start.sh` and `docs/onboarding/dev-to-prod-runbook.md` to construct `DATABASE_URL` for the dev DB via the proxy.\
  - Example pattern: `NEXUS_2025_DEV-v2`.\
\
- `DATABASE_URL`  \
  - The critical variable that tells Prisma and the API which Cloud SQL instance to hit.\
  - Pattern (via proxy on 127.0.0.1:5433):\
    - `postgresql://postgres:<PASSWORD>@127.0.0.1:5433/nexus_db`\
  - Must be set before:\
    - `./scripts/dev-api-cloud-db.sh`\
    - `./scripts/db-migrate-cloud.sh`\
    - Prisma CLI commands in `packages/database`.\
\
- `REDIS_URL`  \
  - Intentionally **unset** for local dev in `scripts/dev-start.sh` so Redis falls back to a no-op client and dev doesn\'92t require Redis.\
\
These env vars are the \'93source of truth\'94 at runtime. The scripts below assume they\'92re set correctly.\
\
---\
\
### 2.2 Dev orchestration scripts (the main env glue)\
\
All under `scripts/` at repo root:\
\
1. `scripts/dev-start.sh`  \
   - **Role:** One\uc0\u8209 shot launcher for your full local dev stack using **Cloud SQL dev via proxy**.\
   - What it does environmentally:\
     - Unsets `REDIS_URL` so Redis is effectively disabled in dev.\
     - Ensures `apps/web/.env.local` exists with:\
```text\
       NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000\
```\
     - Starts **Cloud SQL Auth Proxy** on `127.0.0.1:5433` targeting `nexus-dev-postgres`, using:\
       - `CLOUD_SQL_PROXY_CREDENTIAL_FILE` if set, else ADC.\
     - For the API dev server & worker:\
       - Requires `DEV_DB_PASSWORD` to be exported.\
       - Exports `DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:$\{DEV_DB_PASSWORD\}@127.0.0.1:5433/nexus_db"` before starting:\
         - `./scripts/dev-api-cloud-db.sh` (API on port 8000)\
         - `npm run worker:dev` in `apps/api` (worker)\
     - Starts Next.js dev in `apps/web` (port 3000).\
\
2. `scripts/dev-clean-env.sh`  \
   - **Role:** Hard reset of your local dev environment.\
   - Environment responsibilities:\
     - Kills any `cloud-sql-proxy`, API (ts-node-dev), worker, and Next.js processes.\
     - Verifies ports `3000` (web), `8000` (API), `5433` (proxy) are free.\
     - Then runs `./scripts/dev-start.sh` to rebuild the environment cleanly.\
\
3. `scripts/dev-api-cloud-db.sh`  \
   - **Role:** Run the API dev server against whichever DB `DATABASE_URL` points to.\
   - Contract:\
     - Exits if `DATABASE_URL` is not set.\
     - Doesn\'92t set `DATABASE_URL` itself \'97 it trusts environment (you or other scripts) to set it.\
\
4. `scripts/db-migrate-cloud.sh`  \
   - **Role:** Run Prisma migrations against Cloud SQL (typically dev DB) using `DATABASE_URL`.\
   - Contract:\
     - Requires `DATABASE_URL` set to Cloud SQL via proxy.\
     - `cd` into `packages/database` and runs `npm run prisma:migrate`, so Prisma picks up `DATABASE_URL`.\
\
5. `scripts/dev-restart-cloud.sh`  \
   - **Role:** \'93Quick restart\'94 of a local stack wired to Cloud SQL via `DATABASE_URL`.\
   - Contract:\
     - Requires `DATABASE_URL` set (dev or prod Cloud SQL).\
     - Cleans ports via `./scripts/dev-clean.sh` (separate script).\
     - Restarts API (via `dev-api-cloud-db.sh`) and web (`npm run dev` in `apps/web`).\
\
6. `scripts/dev-stop.sh`  \
   - **Role:** Cleanly stop dev\uc0\u8209 time processes.\
   - Environment\uc0\u8209 related:\
     - Kills `cloud-sql-proxy` on port 5433 (currently wired to `nexusprod-v2` in this script).\
     - Kills API dev server and web dev server processes.\
\
These scripts **encode how your environment should look** (which ports, which DB, which app URLs) and depend on a small set of env vars you manage outside the repo.\
\
---\
\
### 2.3 Web app environment file\
\
- `apps/web/.env.local`  \
  - Created automatically by `scripts/dev-start.sh` if missing.\
  - Key variable:\
    - `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000`\
  - This is what keeps the web dev server and local API in sync \'97 the web app reads this at build/dev time and calls the correct API origin.\
\
If you ever change API port or scheme, this is the file you\'92d adjust (or regenerate via `dev-start.sh`).\
\
---\
\
### 2.4 Database & infra config\
\
- `infra/docker/docker-compose.yml`  \
  - Defines **optional** local Postgres + Redis containers:\
    - `postgres` exposed as `5433 -> 5432`\
    - `redis` exposed as `6380 -> 6379`\
  - When you\'92re using the **GCP Cloud SQL proxy**, this is mostly an alternative path (local DB instead of Cloud SQL). It\'92s still part of the overall \'93environment story\'94, but not typically active when you follow the Cloud SQL proxy golden path.\
\
- `packages/database/prisma/schema.prisma` and `packages/database/prisma/migrations/*`  \
  - These define the **shape** of the DB your Cloud SQL instance must have.\
  - They don\'92t set env vars, but they are the schema that `DATABASE_URL` points to, and they\'92re applied via Prisma commands that read `DATABASE_URL`.\
\
---\
\
### 2.5 Documentation as environment contracts\
\
These docs are effectively \'93living specs\'94 for your environment; they\'92re worth treating as first\uc0\u8209 class references when building your diagram.\
\
- `docs/onboarding/dev-stack.md`  \
  - Defines the **three core processes**: Cloud SQL proxy, API dev server, web dev server.\
  - Provides canonical commands for:\
    - Starting `cloud-sql-proxy` on port 5433.\
    - Exporting `DATABASE_URL` for prod or dev DB.\
    - Booting API + web and verifying `/health`.\
\
- `docs/onboarding/envs-and-migrations.md`  \
  - Explains the mapping between:\
    - `cloud-sql-proxy` instance arguments (dev vs prod).\
    - The exact `DATABASE_URL` strings you should use for dev vs prod.\
  - Codifies the rule: schema work and experiments \uc0\u8594  dev DB; prod changes only via `migrate deploy`.\
\
- `docs/onboarding/dev-to-prod-runbook.md`  \
  - Defines the canonical **day\uc0\u8209 to\u8209 day local startup** with dev DB:\
    - Start proxy to `nexus-dev-postgres` on 5433.\
    - Export `DEV_DB_PASSWORD` and run `./scripts/dev-clean-env.sh`, which in turn orchestrates `dev-start.sh`.\
  - Also documents the prod migration and deploy pipeline (less relevant for pure local dev, but important for the full picture).\
\
