## 3. How to think about this when drawing your diagram\
\
When you sketch this out (Miro, Excalidraw, paper), I\'92d include four layers:\
\
1. **GCP layer**\
   - Cloud SQL instances: `nexus-dev-postgres`, `nexusprod-v2`.\
   - (Optional for full picture) Cloud Run services and Vercel, but those are more prod than local dev.\
\
2. **Proxy layer (GCP proxy)**\
   - One box: **Cloud SQL Auth Proxy** on your Mac.\
   - Annotations:\
     - Listens on `127.0.0.1:5433`.\
     - Started manually or via `scripts/dev-start.sh` / docs commands.\
     - Requires `CLOUD_SQL_PROXY_CREDENTIAL_FILE` or ADC.\
\
3. **Local services layer**\
   - API dev server (`apps/api`, port 8000).\
   - API worker (BullMQ jobs, also `apps/api`).\
   - Web dev server (`apps/web`, port 3000).\
\
4. **Configuration & environment layer**\
   - *Shell*: `DATABASE_URL`, `DEV_DB_PASSWORD`, `CLOUD_SQL_PROXY_CREDENTIAL_FILE`, optional `REDIS_URL`.\
   - *Repo scripts*: the `scripts/*.sh` files above.\
   - *Env file*: `apps/web/.env.local` with `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL`.\
   - *Schema*: Prisma schema + migrations in `packages/database/prisma/*`.\
